100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 3, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing rising tensions in Europe and discussing disarmament efforts. In the United States, the trial of the Scopes Monkey Trial continued to draw national attention, as debates over teaching evolution in schools intensified. Meanwhile, the British government faced criticism over its handling of the ongoing unrest in India, where calls for independence grew louder.
